  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>Senior Software Engineer with 8+ years building and operating backend systems. I share how real systems behave, AI in practice, and the engineering and product judgment behind good decisions.</p>

  <h2>What I Do</h2>
  <p>I build reliable services with clear contracts, strong observability, and practical tooling. My focus is production systems: how they work, how they fail, and how to debug them.</p>

  <h2>Engineering Areas</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>APIs & services</strong> — contracts, performance, migrations</li>
    <li><strong>Data & search</strong> — PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Elasticsearch</li>
    <li><strong>Reliability & observability</strong> — SLOs, metrics, logs, traces</li>
    <li><strong>Developer tooling</strong> — automation, developer experience, CI</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Current Stack</h2>
  <p><strong>Languages</strong>: Ruby, Go, Java, Python</p>
  <p><strong>Infrastructure & data</strong>: PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Elasticsearch, Redis, Aerospike, Kafka, Kubernetes</p>
  <p><strong>Observability</strong>: Prometheus, Grafana, Datadog, OpenTelemetry</p>

  <h2>Public Work</h2>
  <p><strong>Writing</strong>: I've written for <a href="https://signoz.io/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">SigNoz</a>, <a href="https://geekflare.com/author/debanjan/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Geekflare</a>, and <a href="https://theybanjan.medium.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Medium</a> about monitoring, backend architecture, and production systems.</p>
  <p><strong>Projects</strong>:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://github.com/debanjanc01/letter" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"><strong>letter</strong></a> — Go tool for updating Postman collections from locally saved files</li>
    <li><a href="https://github.com/debanjanc01/bytecase" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"><strong>bytecase</strong></a> — collection of useful code snippets and scripts</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Engineering Principles</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Clarity over cleverness</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Measure impact and make it observable</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Design for on-call</strong>: account for idempotency, backpressure, and timeouts</li>
    <li><strong>Prefer small, reversible steps</strong></li>
    <li>Prefer boring technology that scales</li>
    <li>Prefer fast feedback loops</li>
    <li>Prefer documents that age well</li>
  </ul>

